			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Actually, as a happy user of ASM6 myself, I may migrate back to using NESASM because of the non-auto ZP thing. I'm interested in PCE development, and may reuse some of the codes if possible, so <em>not</em> being able to automatically force ZP addressing is a <em>necessity</em> (as the ZP on PCE Hu6280 starts from $2000, not $0000, and also, stack is at $2100).<br /><br />The best of both worlds, though, is to have a switch (either in command line or an assembler directive) to turn on or off whether ZP address modes are auto. I think there're some unofficial versions of NESASM that actually do this.<br /><br />Or even better, someone takes the time to add Hu6280 (thus automatically also 65C02) support to ASM6, and add the switch mentioned above also.</div>

